1
00:00:05,529 --> 00:00:32,521
欢迎来到栖目See Movie私人影院

2
00:01:45,036 --> 00:01:47,008
《此时》读者见面会 作者：杰西·华莱士

3
00:01:47,057 --> 00:01:49,651
你认为这本书算自传式的吗？

4
00:01:51,094 --> 00:01:53,153
这个...
Well, I mean...

5
00:01:53,330 --> 00:01:56,163
...什么书不是自传式的呢？
...isn't everything autobiographical?

6
00:01:56,333 --> 00:02:00,793
我们都是通过自己那小小的钥匙孔 看外面的世界，对吧？
I mean, we all see the world through our own tiny keyhole, right?

7
00:02:01,004 --> 00:02:02,904
我是说，我总想起汤玛斯·沃尔夫说的
I mean, I always think of Thomas Wolfe.

8
00:02:03,106 --> 00:02:06,371
你看过“天使望故乡”那本书 前面那短短一页的“致读者”吗？
Have you ever seen that little one-page "Note to Reader"...

9
00:02:06,543 --> 00:02:08,670
你知道我在说什么吧？
<i>...in the front of Look Homeward, Angel?</i>

10
00:02:09,446 --> 00:02:14,383
总之，他说我们的生命就是 由点点滴滴集合而成的
Anyway, he says that we are the sum of all the moments of our lives...

11
00:02:14,551 --> 00:02:18,351
...而任何人坐下来，写出来的 都不过是自己生命中的体验...
...and anybody who sits down to write will use the clay of their own life...

12
00:02:18,522 --> 00:02:20,046
...谁都无法回避
...that you can't avoid that.

13
00:02:20,223 --> 00:02:25,126
所以当我审视我的人生， 我必须得承认，我发现...
So when I look at my own life, I have to admit, right, that I...

14
00:02:25,429 --> 00:02:29,923
我从来没有经历过枪林弹雨 或是暴力事件，起码没真正体验过
I've never been around a bunch of guns or violence, you know, not really.

15
00:02:30,133 --> 00:02:34,069
没有什么政治阴谋， 也没什么直升机失事
No political intrigue or a helicopter crash, right?

16
00:02:34,705 --> 00:02:38,766
但是我的人生，从我个人观点来看 仍然是富有戏剧性的
But my life, from my own point of view, has been full of drama, right?

17
00:02:39,409 --> 00:02:41,877
于是我想也许我也能写本书...
And so I thought, if I could write a book...

18
00:02:42,079 --> 00:02:46,482
...记录下我见到某人时的感觉
...that could capture what it's like to really meet somebody...

19
00:02:46,717 --> 00:02:49,379
我是说，我经历过的最刺激的事情之一
One of the most exciting things that's happened to me...

20
00:02:49,553 --> 00:02:51,851
...就是真正和某人见面， 让两个人心灵相通
...is to meet somebody, make that connection.

21
00:02:52,055 --> 00:02:56,082
而如果我能把它表现出来 你明白吗，抓住那一刻的感觉...
And if I could make that valuable, you know, to capture that...

22
00:02:56,760 --> 00:03:00,059
...那就是我的写作意图了，亦或者....
...that would be the attempt, or...

23
00:03:00,597 --> 00:03:03,088
你满意我的回答吗？
Did I answer your question?

24
00:03:03,667 --> 00:03:06,101
我干脆就直说吧...
I'll try to be more specific.

25
00:03:06,570 --> 00:03:09,266
我在火车上遇见一个年轻的法国女郎
Was there ever a French young woman on a train you met...

26
00:03:09,439 --> 00:03:11,771
并和她共度良宵
...and spent an evening with?

27
00:03:15,645 --> 00:03:18,580
这个，对我来说...我是说...
See, to me, that... I mean...

28
00:03:18,749 --> 00:03:22,185
- ...这并不重要，你懂吗？ - 就是说的确有了？
...that's not important, you know? - So that's a yes?

29
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:27,113
好吧，既然我人在法国，这又是 我签名售书的最后一站，那就算有吧
All right, since I'm in France and this is the last stop of my book tour, yes.

30
00:03:27,924 --> 00:03:29,755
谢谢
Thank you.

31
00:03:29,926 --> 00:03:33,327
华莱士先生，这本书的结尾给我们留下了悬念
Mr. Wallace, the book ends on an ambiguous note.

32
00:03:33,497 --> 00:03:34,828
我们不知道
We don't know.

33
00:03:35,031 --> 00:03:37,625
你认为他们六个月之后会重聚吗？
Do you think they get back together in six months...

34
00:03:37,901 --> 00:03:41,268
就像他们彼此承诺的那样？
...like they promise each other?

35
00:03:41,905 --> 00:03:43,805
像他们保证的？
Like they promised?

36
00:03:45,409 --> 00:03:48,105
我认为这个问题实际上是，是个....
I think how you answer that, you know, is...

37
00:03:48,945 --> 00:03:52,210
是个很好的测试，看看你到底是 喜欢浪漫还是对它嗤之以鼻
It's a good test, right, if you're a romantic or a cynic.

38
00:03:52,449 --> 00:03:56,442
我是说，你认为他们会重聚的，对吧？
Right? I mean, you think they get back together, right?

39
00:03:56,620 --> 00:03:58,144
- 显然你并不这么认为 - 是的
- You don't, for sure. - No.

40
00:03:58,321 --> 00:04:00,312
还是你希望他们会 不过你无法肯定
And you hope they do, but you're not sure.

41
00:04:00,524 --> 00:04:04,187
- 所以你才问这个问题 - 你认为他们会重聚吗？
- That's why you're asking the question. - Do you think they get back together?

42
00:04:04,428 --> 00:04:06,521
我是说你们重聚了吗？ 在现实生活中？
I mean, did you in real life?

43
00:04:07,998 --> 00:04:09,829
现实生活中...？
Did I in real...?

44
00:04:10,200 --> 00:04:12,794
要用我祖父的话来说啊
Look, in the words of my grandfather, okay:

45
00:04:12,969 --> 00:04:16,063
天晓得会不会
"To answer that would take the piss out of the whole thing. "

46
00:04:16,973 --> 00:04:20,465
我们的时间只够问最后一个问题了
We just have the time for one last question.

47
00:04:20,677 --> 00:04:22,372
你下一本书将是什么？
What is your next book?

48
00:04:24,981 --> 00:04:27,472
我不知道，老兄，我真的不知道...
I don't know, man. I don't know.

49
00:04:27,717 --> 00:04:31,175
我一直...一直在考虑这个构思...
I've been... I've been thinking about this...

50
00:04:31,354 --> 00:04:34,050
我总是想写本书...
Well, I always kind of wanted to write a book...

51
00:04:34,224 --> 00:04:37,887
...一切都发生在一首流行歌曲那么长时间内
...that all took place within the space of a pop song.

52
00:04:38,094 --> 00:04:41,222
总共大概3到4分钟吧
Like three or four minutes long, the whole thing.

53
00:04:41,465 --> 00:04:44,957
整个故事大概是说有个男人...
The story, the idea, is that there's this guy, right...

54
00:04:45,168 --> 00:04:47,864
...他非常的沮丧，因为...
...and he's totally depressed.

55
00:04:48,071 --> 00:04:52,235
他最大的梦想就是拥有一段 轰轰烈烈的爱情，一次冒险...
His great dream was to be a lover, an adventurer, you know...

56
00:04:52,409 --> 00:04:55,173
...比如开着摩托周游南美
...riding motorcycles through South America.

57
00:04:55,378 --> 00:04:58,108
但是事实上他只是坐在大理石桌前吃着龙虾
And instead he's sitting at a marble table eating lobster.

58
00:04:58,281 --> 00:05:01,375
他有份不错的工作，妻子也很漂亮
He's got a good job and a beautiful wife, right, but that...

59
00:05:01,551 --> 00:05:04,918
他应有尽有，但是这并不是他真正想要的...
Everything that he needs. But that doesn't matter...

60
00:05:05,121 --> 00:05:08,090
...因为他真正想要的是为某种理想而战
...because what he wants is to fight for meaning.

61
00:05:08,358 --> 00:05:10,588
你明白吗，快乐来自于过程
You know? Happiness is in the doing, right?

62
00:05:10,794 --> 00:05:13,092
而不是因为你得到了你想要的东西
Not in the getting what you want.

63
00:05:13,296 --> 00:05:16,788
总之，他坐在那里，突然间...
So he's sitting there, and just that second...

64
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:21,232
...他五岁的小女儿跳上了桌子
...his little 5-year-old daughter hops up on the table.

65
00:05:21,404 --> 00:05:24,703
他知道她该下来，因为她可能会受伤
And he knows that she should get down, because she could get hurt.

66
00:05:24,908 --> 00:05:29,607
但是她正穿着夏日的裙子 随着那首歌翩翩起舞
But she's dancing to this pop song in a summer dress.

67
00:05:30,247 --> 00:05:32,238
然后一晃眼
And he looks down...

68
00:05:32,449 --> 00:05:34,940
...突然间，他回到了十六岁
...and all of a sudden, he's 6.

69
00:05:35,785 --> 00:05:41,246
他的高中女友正送他回家
And his high-school sweetheart is dropping him off at home.

70
00:05:41,424 --> 00:05:44,985
而他们刚刚度过了他们的初夜 她很爱他...
And they just lost their virginity, and she loves him...

71
00:05:45,161 --> 00:05:49,120
...而汽车收音机里里播放着的 是同样的一首曲子
...and the same song is playing on the car radio.

72
00:05:49,399 --> 00:05:52,334
然后她爬上了车顶，开始在那里跳舞
And she climbs up and starts dancing on the roof of the car.

73
00:05:52,569 --> 00:05:54,093
这一下，他开始很担心她！
And now he's worried about her.

74
00:05:54,271 --> 00:05:58,571
她很美，表情也竟然和她女儿一模一样
And she's beautiful, with a facial expression just like his daughter's.

75
00:05:58,909 --> 00:06:01,070
事实上，这可能就是 他为什么会喜欢她的原因
In fact, maybe that's why he even likes her.

76
00:06:01,278 --> 00:06:04,179
你懂吗，他知道他并不是身处回忆之中...
You see, he knows he's not remembering this dance...

77
00:06:04,414 --> 00:06:08,111
...而是他就在那里，他同时 出现在人生的两个场景之中
...he's there. He's there, in both moments, simultaneously.

78
00:06:08,318 --> 00:06:11,754
就在这一瞬间，他全部的人生 好像都交汇到了一起
And just for an instant, all his life is just folding in on itself.

79
00:06:11,955 --> 00:06:14,651
对他来说，时间明显是个谎言
And it's obvious to him that time is a lie.

80
00:06:16,960 --> 00:06:19,428
因为那一刻将一直延伸下去...
That it's all happening all the time...

81
00:06:19,596 --> 00:06:23,157
..而且.每个时刻之内都包含着另一个时刻...
...and inside every moment is another moment...

82
00:06:23,433 --> 00:06:25,264
...一切的一切，都发生在同一瞬间
...all happening simultaneously.

83
00:06:25,468 --> 00:06:28,562
总之，这就是我大概的想法，总之
Anyway, that's kind of the idea. Anyway.

84
00:06:29,873 --> 00:06:32,273
我们的作者很快就得去机场了...
Our author has to be going to the airport soon...

85
00:06:32,475 --> 00:06:35,376
...那么，谢谢各位今天下午光临
...so thank you all very much for coming over this afternoon.

86
00:06:35,612 --> 00:06:38,843
尤其要感谢华莱士先生和我们 共度了这么美好的一个下午
And a special thanks to Mr. Wallace for being with us.

87
00:06:39,082 --> 00:06:40,481
谢谢，谢谢
Thank you. Thank you.

88
00:06:40,650 --> 00:06:43,346
希望你出下本书的时候 我们还能在这见到你！
We hope to see you here again with your next book.

89
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:45,500
（法语）感谢大家光临

90
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:49,000
（法语）我们为大家准备了香槟和一些小点心

91
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,000
（法语）请尽情享受吧
Thank you all. How much longer before I have to go to the airport?

92
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:53,327
谢谢各位，我必须在几点之前去机场？

93
00:06:53,496 --> 00:06:55,123
哦，你必须在七点半之前离开？
Oh, you should leave at 7:30...

94
00:06:55,365 --> 00:06:57,890
- 最迟七点半！ - 好
- Seven-thirty at the very latest. - Okay.

95
00:07:02,806 --> 00:07:06,139
- 嗨 - 你好
- Hi. - Hello.

96
00:07:08,745 --> 00:07:11,475
- 你还好吗？ - 很好，你呢？
- How are you? - Good, and you?

97
00:07:13,249 --> 00:07:16,047
挺好，是的，我很好，我...
I'm good, yeah, I'm great. I'm...

98
00:07:16,853 --> 00:07:19,185
你愿意...我是说...去喝杯咖啡什么的吗？
Do you wanna, maybe, get a cup of coffee?

99
00:07:19,923 --> 00:07:22,391
他不是说你要赶飞机吗？
Didn't he just say you have a plane to catch?

100
00:07:23,426 --> 00:07:26,361
是啊...不过时间还早
Yeah. But, I mean, I have a little time.

101
00:07:26,730 --> 00:07:30,029
- 那好吧 - 好吗？好，那，让我....
- Okay. - Yeah? All right, well, let me...

102
00:07:30,233 --> 00:07:32,326
我在外面等你
I'll meet you outside. Okay.

103
00:07:34,070 --> 00:07:36,436
我出去一下，喝杯咖啡
Excuse me. I'm just gonna go get a cup of coffee.

104
00:07:36,673 --> 00:07:38,903
- 我七点一刻回来 - 这些书你都签了名吗？
- I'll be back at 7: 5. - Did you sign all these?

105
00:07:39,075 --> 00:07:41,703
- 是的，我肯定签了 - 拿着你的司机菲利普的名片...
- Yeah, I sure did. - Get your driver Philippe's card...

106
00:07:41,911 --> 00:07:44,402
...这样你要是晚了，就用手机给他打电话
...so you can call his cell if you're running late.

107
00:07:44,648 --> 00:07:47,208
我们会把你的包放在车里 这样你就不会晚了
We'll put your bags in the car so you're not late.

108
00:07:47,417 --> 00:07:49,942
- 好的，谢谢你 - （法语）非常感谢
- All right, thanks for everything. - Thank you.

109
00:07:52,288 --> 00:07:54,256
谁是菲利普？
Which one's Philippe?

110
00:07:53,500 --> 00:07:56,900
（法语）菲利普，把你的名片给他， 上面有你的手机号码

111
00:07:56,900 --> 00:07:57,900
（法语）谢谢

112
00:08:12,208 --> 00:08:15,541
- 真难以置信你会在这里 - 我就住在巴黎
- I can't believe you're here. - I live here in Paris.

113
00:08:16,946 --> 00:08:20,279
你真的不用多呆几天吗？ 你不用再和谁谈什么了吗？
Are you sure you don't have to stay? You're not supposed to talk more?

114
00:08:20,483 --> 00:08:22,542
不，他们都开始烦我了 我昨晚整夜都在这里
They're sick of me. I spent the night here.

115
00:08:22,752 --> 00:08:26,085
- 哦，真的吗？ - 是啊，他们楼上有间阁楼
- You did? - Yeah, they got a loft upstairs.

116
00:08:26,456 --> 00:08:28,822
- 你怎么样？这感觉真奇怪 - 我很好
- How are you? This is so weird. - I'm fine.

117
00:08:29,059 --> 00:08:32,756
- 见到你真高兴！ - 见到你真高兴！
- It's good to see you. - It's good to see you.

118
00:08:35,131 --> 00:08:37,565
- 那你想去喝杯咖啡吗？ - 哦，当然
- So you want to go to a caf? - Yeah.

119
00:08:37,767 --> 00:08:40,133
那好，那边不远有一家很不错
Okay. There's one a little further that I like.

120
00:08:40,303 --> 00:08:44,205
我刚才见到你的时候我都快傻了
I thought I was gonna totally lose it in there when I first saw you.

121
00:08:44,407 --> 00:08:46,136
你怎么会知道我会来这的呢？
How did you know I was gonna be here?

122
00:08:46,342 --> 00:08:50,745
这是我在巴黎最喜欢的书店了 你可以坐在那里看一天书
It's my favorite bookstore in Paris. You can sit down for hours and read.

123
00:08:50,914 --> 00:08:52,905
我很喜欢这样，那儿是有跳蚤，不过，你知道的....
I love it. There's fleas, but, you know...

124
00:08:53,083 --> 00:08:55,449
我知道，我简直感觉昨晚有只猫睡在我头上
I know. I think a cat slept on my head last night.

125
00:08:55,618 --> 00:08:58,246
我一个月前就书店日历上看到你的照片
I saw your picture on the calendar about a month ago...

126
00:08:58,421 --> 00:09:00,286
知道你会来这里
...and that you were going to be here.

127
00:09:00,724 --> 00:09:03,625
有意思的是，我读了你的书，一小段而已
It's funny, because I read an article on your book...

128
00:09:03,793 --> 00:09:07,786
- 我有种朦朦胧胧的的亲切感 - 朦朦胧胧？是吗？
...and it sounded vaguely familiar. - Vaguely? Yeah.

129
00:09:08,164 --> 00:09:11,998
是的，只不过是在见到你的照片 之后才有的，所以...
But I didn't put it all together until I saw your photo. So...

130
00:09:12,168 --> 00:09:14,329
你看过那书了吗？
Did you have a chance to read it?

131
00:09:14,537 --> 00:09:15,970
是的，我....
Yes, I...

132
00:09:16,139 --> 00:09:18,607
你的书让我感到惊喜，你应该体会得到的
I was really, really surprised, as you can imagine.

133
00:09:18,808 --> 00:09:21,436
我是说，我对它爱不释手
I mean, I had to read it twice, actually.

134
00:09:21,644 --> 00:09:23,669
- 是吗？ - 是的
- Yeah? - Yeah.

135
00:09:23,900 --> 00:09:25,100
（法语）写得马马虎虎？
No, I liked it. It's very romantic.

136
00:09:25,115 --> 00:09:27,709
不，我很喜欢，非常浪漫！

137
00:09:27,884 --> 00:09:30,546
我平时不爱看类似的书 但是你写的真好
I usually don't like that, but it's really well-written.

138
00:09:30,787 --> 00:09:33,779
- 写的非常好，祝贺你！ - 好吧，谢谢
- It's well-written. Congratulations. - All right. Thank you.

139
00:09:34,190 --> 00:09:36,055
- 等等 - 怎么啦？
- Wait. - What?

140
00:09:36,292 --> 00:09:40,251
在我们出发前，我得问你...
Before we go anywhere, I have to ask you...

141
00:09:40,663 --> 00:09:42,221
没问题，什么事？
Sure. What?

142
00:09:42,398 --> 00:09:45,390
那年十二月，你去维也纳了吗？
Did you show up in Vienna that December?

143
00:09:47,270 --> 00:09:51,639
- 呃，你去了吗？ - 没有，我没能去成，但是...你去了吗？
- Did you? - No, I couldn't. But did you?

144
00:09:51,808 --> 00:09:55,175
- 我必须要知道，这对我很重要！ - 为什么，既然你都没去？
- I need to know. It's important to me. - Why, if you didn't?

145
00:09:55,545 --> 00:09:57,536
那，你去了吗？
Well, did you?

146
00:09:57,714 --> 00:09:59,204
没有
No.

147
00:10:00,850 --> 00:10:02,340
哦，谢天谢地你没去！
Thank God you didn't.

148
00:10:02,552 --> 00:10:04,349
- 哦，天啊 - 谢天谢地你没去
- Oh, my God. - Thank God you didn't.

149
00:10:04,554 --> 00:10:08,046
我是说，幸亏我没去，你也没去 要是我们两个只有一个人去了...
